# Domain rules

## Purpose

Domain contains the core business logic of the application.

## Strict rules

- Domain must contain pure functions only
- No side effects (no storage, no API calls, no timers)
- No access to UI
- No access to external services

## Function design

- Functions must be small and focused
- Each function should do one thing
- Use descriptive names (createTask, validateUser)

## Data handling

- Do not mutate inputs
- Always return new objects
- Validate input before processing

## Forbidden

- localStorage
- database access
- fetch / network
- UI logic

-----------
## Storage (Infra Layer)

### Purpose
Responsible for data persistence.

### Rules
- Can access localStorage
- Must not contain business logic
- Should be simple (save/load/update)

## When unsure

Ask before adding anything that is not pure logic.
